visual.description: Use to visualise the distribution of your data.

en-US.Roles_Sampling_Description: The level you wish to aggregate your measure data at, to prevent incorrect aggregation prior to plotting.
en-US.Roles_Measure_Description: The values you wish to observe in your violin plot for each category.
en-US.Roles_Category_Description: The category that you wish to group your data into.
en-US.Objects_DataLimit_Description:
By default, custom visuals can display a maximum of 30,000 rows. If you have more than this in the data you want to visualise, then these options allow you to override the default limit     .

: anything that updates the visual (data, properties) can be costly. If you are making interim changes to your visual, it is recommended that you turn these options off while doing that, and re-enable them when you're finished.
en-US.Objects_DataLimit_Override_Description:
Allow loading of additional data from the model to the visual, if it is available.

Note that Power BI still may not be able to supply all data to your visual, depending on memory constraints.
en-US.Objects_DataLimit_ShowProgress_Descripti: Display information and explanation when fetching more data from the model if the row limit is exceeded.
en-US.Objects_DataLimit_ShowCustomVisualNotes_:
Display information about the custom visual limitations and recommendations for end users.

This option allows you to turn this info off for end-users if you feel it is not relevant to them.
en-US.Objects_Violin_Description: Configure how the violin (Kernel Density Estimation/KDE) plot is displayed in your report.
en-US.Objects_Violin_InnerPadding_Description: Amount of padding to apply from the edge of the series.
en-US.Objects_Violin_StrokeWidth_Description: Width of the lines bordering the violin plot.
en-US.Objects_Violin_Clamp_Description:
If enabled, this will terminate the KDE plot at the min and max values of the data set for each category, and not plot the tail of the series.

Note that in some cases this may not reliably communicate the distribution or modality of your data.
en-US.Objects_Violin_SamplingResolution_Descri: Specify how densely the data should be sampled when calculating its distribution.
en-US.Objects_Violin_Kernel_Description: The kernel function to use when calculating density estimation.
en-US.Objects_Violin_SpecifyBandwidth_Descript:
If disabled, this will automatically estimate the "rule-of-thumb" KDE bandwidth.

Enable this to manually specify your own value(s).
en-US.Objects_Violin_Bandwidth_Description:
Manually provided KDE bandwidth value to apply to all data.

If using Bandwidth By Category, then this will serve as the default for all categories that don't have a bandwidth explicitly set.
en-US.Objects_Violin_BandwidthByCategory_Descr:
If disabled, the same KDE bandwidth value will be applied across all categories.

If enabled, the bandwidth will be estimated or can be specified for each category, as applicable.
en-US.Objects_Violin_CategoryBandwidth_Descrip:
Specified bandwidth value for this category.

If this has not been explicitly set, then this will inherit from the Bandwidth value above.

To revert to the default value (if you have already specified it), then clear the field value and it will be replaced with the Bandwidth value.
en-US.Objects_Sorting_Description: Sorting options for displayed categories within the plot.
en-US.Objects_Sorting_By_Description: Specify how to sort the displayed categories in the visual.
en-US.Objects_Sorting_Order_Description: The order/direction in which to sort.
en-US.Objects_DataColours_Description: Colors to apply to the violin plot, or multiple plot categories.
en-US.Objects_DataColours_DefaultFillColour_De: Color to apply to all categories in the chart.
en-US.Objects_DataColours_Transparency_Descrip: Level of transparency to apply to the violin fill.
en-US.Objects_DataColours_CategoryFillColour_D: Fill color for this particular category.
en-US.Objects_DataColours_ColourByCategory_Des: Apply specific fill color to invididual categories.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_Description: Provides an accompanying plot to the violin.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_PlotType_Description:
The type of combo plot to display:

 - 'Barcode (Strip)' shows a plot of individual data points, using a consistent width.
 - 'Box' shows distribution of data using a box and whisker plot.
 - 'Column (Min/Max)' shows a ranged plot from minimum to maximum.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_StrokeWidth_Descripti: Width of the lines used in the selected combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_BoxFillColour_Descrip: Fill color to apply to the combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_BarColour_Description: Color to apply to the data bars in the combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_Transparency_Descript: Level of transparency to apply to the combo plot fill.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_InnerPadding_Descript: Amount of padding to apply from the edge of the violin.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_ShowWhiskers_Descript: Show the 5% - 95% confidence interval (whiskers) on the box plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_ShowQuartiles_Descrip: Show 1st & 3rd quartiles, as lines on the diagram.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_Quartile1FillColour_D: Color to apply to the 1st quartile line in the combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_Quartile1StrokeWidth_: Width of the 1st quartile line in the combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_Quartile1StrokeLineSt: The style to apply to the 1st quartile line in the combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_Quartile3FillColour_D: Color to apply to the 3rd quartile line in the combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_Quartile3StrokeWidth_: Width of the 3rd quartile line in the combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_Quartile3StrokeLineSt: The style to apply to the 3rd quartile line in the combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_ShowMedian_Descriptio: Show the median, as a line across the box plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_MedianFillColour_Desc: Color to apply to the median line.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_MedianStrokeLineStyle: Style to apply to the median line.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_ShowMean_Description: Show the mean, as a circle in the combo plot.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_MeanStrokeWidth_Descr: Width of the lines used when displaying the mean.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_MeanFillColour_Descri: The color to apply to the mean indicator.
en-US.Objects_DataPoints_MeanFillColourInner_D: The inner color to apply to the mean indicator.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_TitleStyle_Description: Specify what to display in the Y-Axis title.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_TitleColor_Description: Specify color for the Y-Axis title.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_TitleText_Description: Specify manual text for the Y-Axis title.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_TitleFontSize_Description: Specify size of the Y-Axis title text.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_TitleFontFamily_Descriptio: Specify the font to use for the Y-Axis title.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_Gridlines_Description: Toggle the display of Y-Axis gridlines.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_GridlineColor_Description: Specify the color to apply to Y-Axis gridlines.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_GridlineStrokeWidth_Descri: Specify the width of the Y-Axis gridlines.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_GridlineStrokeLineStyle_De: The style to apply to the Y-Axis gridlines.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_FontColor_Description: Specify color for the Y-Axis labels.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_FontSize_Description: Specify the size of the Y-Axis labels.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_FontFamily_Description: Specify the font to use for the Y-Axis labels.
en-US.Objects_YAxis_Precision_Description: Select the number of decimal places to display for the values.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_FontColor_Description: Specify color for the X-Axis labels.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_FontSize_Description: Specify the size of the X-Axis labels.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_FontFamily_Description: Specify the font to use for the X-Axis labels.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_TitleColor_Description: Specify color for the X-Axis title.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_TitleText_Description: Specify manual text for the X-Axis title.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_TitleFontSize_Description: Specify size of the X-Axis title text.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_TitleFontFamily_Descriptio: Specify the font to use for the X-Axis title.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_Gridlines_Description: Toggle the display of X-Axis gridlines.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_GridlineColor_Description: Specify the color to apply to X-Axis gridlines.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_GridlineStrokeWidth_Descri: Specify the width of the X-Axis gridlines.
en-US.Objects_XAxis_GridlineStrokeLineStyle_De: The style to apply to the X-Axis gridlines.
en-US.Objects_Legend_Position_Description: Select the location for the legend.
en-US.Objects_Legend_TitleText_Description: Specify text for the legend title.
en-US.Objects_Legend_FontColor_Description: Specify color for the legend font.
en-US.Objects_Legend_FontSize_Description: Specify the size of the legend font.
en-US.Objects_Legend_ShowCategories_Descriptio: Show or hide the categories on the legend.
en-US.Objects_Legend_ShowStatisticalPoints_Des: Show or hide the statistical data indicators (mean, median, quartiles).
en-US.Objects_Legend_DataPointText_Description: Text to display on the legend to indicate a single data point.
en-US.Objects_Legend_MedianText_Description: Text to display on the legend to indicate the median.
en-US.Objects_Legend_MeanText_Description: Text to display on the legend to indicate the mean.
en-US.Objects_Legend_QuartileCombinedText_Desc: Text to display on the legend to indicate the 1st & 3rd quartiles (displayed when both quartile indicators have the same formatting).
en-US.Objects_Legend_Quartile1Text_Description: Text to display on the legend to indicate the 1st quartile (displayed when both quartile indicators have differing formatting).
en-US.Objects_Legend_Quartile3Text_Description: Text to display on the legend to indicate the 3rd quartile (displayed when both quartile indicators have differing formatting).
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_Description: If using the default (traditional) tooltip, you can customise the display of data points using this menu.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_NumberSamplesDisplayUnit: Display unit formatting to apply to the # Samples tooltip data point.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_NumberSamplesPrecision_D: If using display units for the # Samples data point, you can use to modify the number of decimal places.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_MeasureDisplayUnits_Desc: Display units to apply to data points utilizing the Measure Data.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_MeasurePrecision_Descrip: If using display units for the Measure Data, you can use to modify the number of decimal places.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_ShowMaxMin_Description: Show the series maximum and minimum values on the tooltip.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_ShowSpan_Description: Show the series span value (range) from minimum to maximum on the tooltip.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_ShowMedian_Description: Show the series median value on the tooltip.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_ShowMean_Description: Show the series mean value on the tooltip.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_ShowDeviation_Descriptio: Show the series standard deviation value on the tooltip.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_ShowQuartiles_Descriptio: Show the series upper and lower quartile values on the tooltip.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_ShowIqr_Description: Show the series inter quartile range value on the tooltip.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_ShowConfidence_Descripti: Show the series confidence values (or whisker values) on the tooltip.
en-US.Objects_Tooltip_ShowBandwidth_Descriptio: Show the bandwidth value applied to the series - used to calculate the violin line.
en-US.Objects_About_VisualName_Description: The name of the custom visual.
en-US.Objects_About_DebugVisualUpdate_Descript: Enable/disable debugging of visual update events.
en-US.Objects_About_DebugProperties_Descriptio: Enable/disable debugging of property change events and values.
